# Add New Screen — Procedure

Every screen has an ID (`S-*`) in `docs/06_SCREEN_CATALOG.md`. UI text **English only**. Security boundary is backend — FE guards are UX (`docs/05` Bölüm 12).

Glob context: `21-frontend-routes.mdc`, `20-frontend-general.mdc`, `22-frontend-forms.mdc`, `23-frontend-rtk-query.mdc`.

## Step 0: Preconditions

- [ ] Screen spec exists in `docs/06_SCREEN_CATALOG.md` (route, layout, auth, component tree, API table, states).
- [ ] Route listed in `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 2.
- [ ] Backend endpoints exist or ship in same PR (`@40-add-new-endpoint`).
- [ ] Shared Zod schemas in `packages/shared` for forms.

Load: `docs/06_SCREEN_CATALOG.md` (target §), `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 2–4, 7, 12–13.

## Step 1: Screen ID and File Placement

| Screen type | Page file | Feature components |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Campaign | `apps/web/src/pages/campaigns/` | `apps/web/src/features/campaigns/` |
| Character | `pages/characters/` | `features/characters/` |
| Homebrew | `pages/homebrew/` | `features/homebrew/` |
| Auth | `pages/auth/` | `features/auth/` |
| Admin | `pages/admin/` | `features/admin/` |

Naming: `CampaignListPage.tsx`, `DmScreenPage.tsx` — PascalCase + `Page` suffix.

## Step 2: Register Route

In router config (`apps/web/src/router/` or `App.tsx` per project layout):

```typescript
{
  path: '/campaigns/:id/dm-screen',
  element: (
    <AuthGuard>
      <DmScreenPage />
    </AuthGuard>
  ),
}
```

Route table reference → `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 2.

| Auth need | Wrapper |
| --- | --- |
| Logged-in | `<AuthGuard>` |
| Admin | `<AuthGuard><AdminGuard>` |
| Public | none or redirect if already logged in |
| Mixed visibility | page-level fetch + 404 UI |

Set dynamic `<title>`: `"DM Screen — DnD Companion"` (`docs/05` Bölüm 13).

## Step 3: Layout

| Layout | When |
| --- | --- |
| `AuthLayout` | login, register, reset password |
| `AppLayout` | authenticated app pages |
| `PublicLayout` | reference, published homebrew gallery |
| `FullWidthLayout` | DM Screen (sidebar hidden) |

Match `docs/06_SCREEN_CATALOG.md` Bölüm 2 and per-screen **Layout** field.

## Step 4: RTK Query Endpoints

In `features/<domain>/<domain>Api.ts`:

```typescript
getCampaign: builder.query<Campaign, string>({
  query: (id) => `/campaigns/${id}`,
  providesTags: (_r, _e, id) => [{ type: 'Campaign', id }],
}),
updateCampaign: builder.mutation<Campaign, { id: string; body: UpdateCampaignDto }>({
  query: ({ id, body }) => ({ url: `/campaigns/${id}`, method: 'PATCH', body }),
  invalidatesTags: (_r, _e, { id }) => [{ type: 'Campaign', id }],
}),
```

- Base URL `/api/v1` in API slice config.
- Bearer token from auth slice (memory — never localStorage).
- Tag strategy → `docs/05` Bölüm 4–5.

## Step 5: Page Component Structure

```typescript
export function CampaignDetailPage() {
  const { id } = useParams();
  const { data, isLoading, isError } = useGetCampaignQuery(id!);

  if (isLoading) return <PageSkeleton />;
  if (isError || !data) return <NotFoundPage />;

  return (
    <AppLayout>
      <CampaignHeader campaign={data.data} />
      <CampaignMemberList campaignId={id!} />
    </AppLayout>
  );
}
```

Implement all UX states from catalog:

| State | Pattern |
| --- | --- |
| Loading | skeleton or spinner |
| Empty | illustrated empty state + CTA |
| Error | Alert with English message from API `message` |
| Success | main content |

## Step 6: Forms (if applicable)

React Hook Form + Zod resolver + shared schema:

```typescript
const form = useForm<CreateCampaignInput>({
  resolver: zodResolver(createCampaignSchema),
});
```

- Validation messages English (`docs/05` Bölüm 7).
- Submit: disable button + spinner.
- Server `400` → map `details[]` to field errors.
- Email-not-verified `403` → toast or banner, not silent fail.

## Step 7: Conditional UI (DM vs Player)

Hide buttons client-side for UX; **never** skip backend checks.

```typescript
const isDm = campaign.ownerId === user?.id;
{isDm && <InviteLinkManager campaignId={id} />}
```

DM-only screens (e.g. `S-DM-SCREEN`) → redirect or 404 if not owner (`docs/06` Grup 3).

## Step 8: Accessibility

Per `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 13 and `25-frontend-a11y.mdc`:

```
[ ] Interactive elements keyboard reachable; focus-visible ring
[ ] Icon buttons have aria-label
[ ] Form fields: label + aria-invalid + aria-describedby on error
[ ] Modals: role="dialog", aria-modal, focus trap
[ ] Color not sole indicator — text/icon accompanies status
```

## Step 9: Responsive Behavior

Follow catalog **Responsive** subsection — typically Tailwind breakpoints (`sm`, `md`, `lg`). DM Screen: players panel stacks on mobile.

## Step 10: Component Tests

Vitest + Testing Library (`docs/08` Bölüm 6):

- Form validation error states (English assert).
- Auth guard redirect (mock store).
- Conditional render (DM-only button hidden for player).

MSW for RTK Query mocks. CSS imports off in vitest config.

## Step 11: Update Docs (if drift)

If route or behavior changed during implementation:

- [ ] `docs/06_SCREEN_CATALOG.md` — component tree, API table
- [ ] `docs/05_FRONTEND_SPEC.md` Bölüm 2 — route row

## Step 12: Pre-PR Verification

```bash
pnpm lint
pnpm typecheck
pnpm --filter web test -- --ci
pnpm --filter web build
```

Checklist:

```
[ ] All UI strings English
[ ] No access token in localStorage/sessionStorage
[ ] Loading/empty/error states implemented
[ ] Screen ID referenced in PR description (e.g. S-DM-SCREEN)
[ ] a11y basics on new interactive elements
```

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Turkish UI labels or toast messages
- ❌ TanStack Query alongside RTK Query
- ❌ Fetch in `useEffect` bypassing RTK Query for CRUD
- ❌ Security-only frontend guard without backend policy
- ❌ Copying full screen catalog tables into components

